1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
XRP over one cycle: up 5x, then down 80%.

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:10,000
Most FXRP yield vaults ride that whole rollercoaster.

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:15,000
RotorVault doesn't: same ballpark return, half the drawdown.

4
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:20,000
-44% instead of -78%, enforced on-chain by Flare's oracle.

5
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:27,000
Deposit FXRP once. An agent proposes how to split it

6
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:33,000
across the live Firelight and Upshift vaults for yield.

7
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:39,000
But every allocation must clear an on-chain FTSOv2 gate.

8
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:45,000
This is the real Coston2 deployment: 5 FXRP, gate risk-off, held idle.

9
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:51,000
Here's what "enforced on-chain" actually means.

10
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:58,000
The agent proposed rebalance(4000, 4000) - 40% Firelight, 40% Upshift.

11
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:04,000
But the gate was risk-off, so the contract overrode it to zero.

12
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:10,000
Rebalanced(0, 0, false) - the veto is in the transaction, not a promise.

13
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:17,000
The Upshift APY comes on-chain via an FDC Web2Json attestation,

14
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:23,000
verified against Flare's FDC and bound to one source URL.

15
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:30,000
And it isn't just stored - rebalance() reads it on-chain.

16
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:35,000
A zero or stale APY forces that venue idle. FDC gates real capital.

17
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:42,000
None of this is mocked.

18
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:48,000
Our adapters are fork-tested against the real Firelight & Upshift vaults.

19
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:55,000
28 contract tests, green against live state, zero API keys.

20
00:01:55,000 --> 00:02:02,000
The strategy isn't a story - it's a keyless, reproducible backtest.

21
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:10,000
Run it with zero API keys and get the same -44% drawdown.

22
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:16,000
Three Flare protocols, all doing real on-chain work:

23
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:22,000
FTSO vetoes, FAssets flows, FDC gates. RotorVault.
